cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.HC 

Reasoning: 
- cs.RO (Robotics) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on effective human-robot interaction and learning from human demonstration. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper proposes a method for compressing high-dimensional sensory data to lower dimensional representations using deep neural networks. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision) is relevant as the experiments involve object data. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is relevant as the paper discusses symbol grounding and aligning learnt representations with semantic notions. 
- cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) is also relevant as the paper focuses on effective human-robot interaction.
